<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewBag.Title - @ViewBag.SiteName</title>
    @Styles.Render("~/Content/css")
    @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/modernizr")

</head>
<body class="clearfix">
<div class="page">
    <div class="page-header">
        <h1 class="masthead">
            <a href="/">@ViewBag.SiteName</a>
        </h1>
        @RenderSection("tagline", required: false)
        <div id="wrapper">
            <ul id="nav">
                <li><a href="/">Confess!</a></li>
                <li>@Html.ActionLink("Indulgences", "List", "Indulgence")</li>
                <li>@Html.ActionLink("Sins", "List", "Sins")</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <p><a href="#" id="what-on-earth">What in heaven is this?<span id="chevron" class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-down" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></p>
        <div class="well hidden" id="about">
            <p>
                In the middle-ages the Catholic church decided that people could have their pergatory reduced if they perform good works. This is called a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indulgence"><em>plenary</em> or <em>papal</em> indulgence</a>. What qualifies as a 'good work' you may ask? Well, among other things, donating money to a <span style="text-decoration: line-through">the church</span> a good cause of course!
            </p>
            <p>So in the middle-ages the plenary indulgence became a method of extracting money from the faithful in exchange for a reduced sentence in the afterlife. It was a fantastic scam. The sale of salvation became big business until in 1567 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indulgence#Late_medieval_abuses">abuse of the practise</a> was so widespread Pope Pius V was compelled to stop the granting of indulgences for money altogether. So the practise stopped... until now!</p>
            <p>We at @ViewBag.SiteName have brought the practise kicking and screaming into the 21st century. You confess to a sin and we'll suggest some charities to make small donation to. Pick one and donate. Then you will receive a genuine* plenary indulgence in PDF format which you can print out and hang on your wall! Pretty neat huh??</p>
            <p>So what are you waiting for? Confess! Donate! Participate in a joke at the expense of the Catholic church! Share this with your friends! Like you have anything better to do!</p>
            <p>
                <small>*genuine doesn't mean it's magical or supernatural in any way</small>
            </p>
            <p>TL;DR: donate to charity for favours in the afterlife.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
            @RenderBody()
    <div id="footer">
        
    </div>
            <div class="push"></div>
        </div>
        <div id="footer-image">
            <div id="god"></div>
        </div>

    @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/jquery")
    @Scripts.Render("~/bundles/bootstrap")
    @RenderSection("scripts", required: false)

<script type="text/javascript">
    $(document).ready(function()
    {
        $('#what-on-earth')
            .click(function () {
            if ($('#about').css('display') == 'none' || $('#about').hasClass('hidden')) {
                $('#about').slideDown();
                $('#about').removeClass('hidden');
                $('#chevron').removeClass('glyphicon-chevron-down');
                $('#chevron').addClass('glyphicon-chevron-up');
            } else {
                $('#about').slideUp();
                $('#chevron').removeClass('glyphicon-chevron-up');
                $('#chevron').addClass('glyphicon-chevron-down');
            }
        });
    });
</script>

<script>
    (function(i,s,o,g,r,a,m){i['GoogleAnalyticsObject']=r;i[r]=i[r]||function(){
        (i[r].q=i[r].q||[]).push(arguments)},i[r].l=1*new Date();a=s.createElement(o),
            m=s.getElementsByTagName(o)[0];a.async=1;a.src=g;m.parentNode.insertBefore(a,m)
    })(window,document,'script','https://www.google-analytics.com/analytics.js','ga');

    ga('create', '@System.Configuration.ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["GoogleAnalyticsTrackingCode"]', 'auto');
    ga('send', 'pageview');

</script>
</body>
</html>
